Organizers of the annual Sportsville Special Recognition Award has announced February 13 as date for this year’s ceremony. Chief Executive Officer of Sportsville, Frank Ilaboya,in a release disclosed that the event which started last year would hold on Sunday, 13 February at the Radisson Hotel in Ikeja, Lagos with funfare. Ilaboya disclosed that some of the nation’s finest sports personalities would be honored at the event.   Burkina Faso 1-1 Gabon (7-6 pens): Ouedraogo hits winning…     Joshua hell bent to reclaim belt from Usyk     Dare praised on tennis tourney for late Soun   “We are excited to announce that all is set for this year’s award ceremony. Some distinguished sports personalities have been selected by our panel to receive awards in various categories this year,” Ilaboya stated, adding Sportsville stands for excellence. Ilaboya, a former chairman of Edo State FA, pointed out that the Sportsville Special Recognition Award was initiated last year to mark the company’s 20th anniversary as the nation’s foremost independent sports production and marketing outfit. - Advertisement - “Clocking 20 years as an independent sports company in Nigeria was a landmark achievement for us, “ noted Ilaboya. “That was why we came up with the award to mark the very important date in our company’s history. “Basically, the award ceremony is our own way of appreciating the effort of those who have contributed to the nation’s sports development over the years,” he added.